Once a pair of stock has passed the cointegration test in either of these scenarios (refer to co-integration test instruction and cointegration test/PLAN.md): 
1) passed both 5yr and 2yr co-integration test
2) passed the co-integration test after the structural break and the period between ZA break day and today is more than 2 years.

To generate trading signals for these two scenarios:
1) passed both 5yr and 2yr co-integration test:
 - identify the parameters: α and β that are used in the 2-year window, trade with this fixed α and β in the trading period and re-estimate the parameters on a monthly basis. If the co-integration test is still a pass after 1 month, use the latest parameters in the latest 2-year window (including the data in the latest month). If the co-integration test is no longer a pass, then stop trading/don't make new transactions.
2) passed the co-integration test after the structural break and the period between ZA break day and today is more than 2 years:
- identify the parameters: α and β that are used in the most recent period with a pass result (most likely ZA break day till today), trade with this fixed α and β in the trading period and re-estimate the parameters on a monthly basis. If the co-integration test is still a pass after 1 month, use the latest parameters in the latest post-break window (including the data in the latest month). If the co-integration test is no longer a pass, then stop trading/don't make new transactions.

For both scenarios when refreshing parameters on a monthly basis, make sure not to use the parameters for that specific 1 month when you trade. Instead, you should include the latest 1-month data and add it to the latest period where it had a co-integration pass result (whether that being 2-year in scenario 1 or post break period till today in scenario 2, so e.g. for β it will be 1) past 1 year and 11 month + 1 month new data that forms the new β or 2) post break period till today + 1 month new data that forms the new β, untill the relationship breaks and co-integration no longer passes.

After above parameters are identified for the trading period coming from these two scenarios, follow below steps:

1. Choose a z-score rolling window of 60–120 days (default 90).

2. Compute spread and half-life at each time t using the fixed α and β:
   spread_t = A_t − (α_q + β_q × B_t)
  Calculate half-life using spread (instead of using either stock individually): ΔSpreadt​=c+θSpreadt−1​+ϵt​, freeze the half-life estimation for the next trading period. Enter a trade only if 3< half-life <40

1. Convert spread into z-score using a rolling window (60–120 days):
   z_t = (spread_t − μ_t) / σ_t
   where μ_t and σ_t are the rolling mean and std of the spread over the chosen window.

2. Generate trading signals:
   1) z < −2  → LONG spread
   2) z >  2  → SHORT spread
   3) |z| < 0.5 → EXIT the trade
   4) otherwise → HOLD


6. Translate signals into actual positions:
   1) z < −2 (LONG spread):  buy A and sell β_q × B
   2) z >  2 (SHORT spread): sell A and buy β_q × B
   Print the translations of these signals based on calculation.

7. Position sizing uses the quarter's fixed β:
   position_B = −β_q × position_A
   β_q does not change day-to-day within a quarter.
   Print the position size.

8. Build daily PnL:
   PnL_t = position_A_{t−1} × ΔA_t + position_B_{t−1} × ΔB_t

9. Kill switch (hard stop)
Disable pair (stock trading the pair, no new transactions) if:
- cointegration test fails: p-value >0.05 in the direction of trading (Y=stock A, X= stock B)
- Half-life doubles or half-life <3 or half-life > 40
- monthly re-estimated β deviates more than 20% from the initial β at the time of the cointegration pass (beta_init). Do NOT compare against a β estimated over a single month's window — that is too noisy and does not measure relationship drift.
- Volatility regime not OK (use this volatility filter: 1) compute 20-day EWMA volatility and 100-day rolling volatility, 2) compute ratio R_t = σ_20​/σ_100. Rules: R< 1.3 normal, 1.3-1.8 suggests halve position size, >1.8 = kill switch/stop trading. Show the volatility regime also on streamlit trading signal tab.